California State Assembly Republican Caucus News index asp Members index asp Members Leadership index html Leadership News index asp News Resources index asp Resources Survey asp Survey Search index asp Search 9 8 03 COX ANNOUNCES TRANSITION PLANS TO ENSURE CONTINUITY OF CAUCUS LEADERSHIP CONTACT Peter DeMarco 916 319 2005 SACRAMENTO Assembly Republican Leader Dave Cox R Fair Oaks today announced the commencement of a long term transition plan for the Assembly Republican Caucus to ensure continuity of caucus operations Under the plan unanimously supported by the Republican Assemblymembers Cox will continue to serve as Leader and fulfill all duties and responsibilities of the position until the first week of January 2004 At that time Assemblyman Kevin McCarthy R Bakersfield will become the new Assembly Republican Leader McCarthy s colleagues unanimously elected him in a caucus meeting today It has been an honor and a privilege to have served California and the members of this Republican caucus as Leader Cox said I look forward to working with Leader Elect Kevin McCarthy over the next four months to ensure a seamless transition I know that he will only strengthen our caucus and build on the many successes we ve enjoyed I have every confidence in his ability to lead and know that he will serve California well in his new role We all owe a tremendous debt of gratitude to Dave Cox for his outstanding leadership Leader Elect McCarthy said He led the fight against higher taxes and runaway spending and provided superior direction for the members of our caucus I am honored to have the full support of my colleagues and will be ever vigilant in upholding the responsibilities of this position California has a bright future and we intend to help restore the glory that made our state the envy of the nation Having trouble with this site mailto republican assembly ca gov e mail the webmaster
